TITLE: Registering Guild Application Commands - Typescript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to register application commands to a specific guild (server) using Discordeno. It imports the `bot` instance and the previously defined `roles` command object. It then uses `bot.rest.upsertGuildApplicationCommands` to register the commands to the specified guild ID.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/website/docs/examples/reactionroles.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
