TITLE: Create a Discord Bot with Node.js
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to create a simple Discord bot using Discordeno in a Node.js environment. It imports the necessary modules, configures the bot with a token from environment variables, defines a ready event handler, and starts the bot.  It requires the `@discordeno/bot` and `dotenv` packages.  The bot token must be available in the environment variables.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/website/docs/examples/node.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import dotenv from 'dotenv'
import { createBot } from '@discordeno/bot'

dotenv.config()

const bot = createBot({
  token: process.env.token,
  events: {
    ready: ({ shardId }) => console.log(`Shard ${shardId} ready`),
  },
})

await bot.start()
```

