TITLE: Forwarding Gateway Requests to a Gateway Manager
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to forward gateway requests (specifically `requestMembers`) to a separate gateway manager process using `fetch`. The request is sent as a POST request with a JSON body containing the request type, guild ID, and options. It sets the `Content-Type` and `Authorization` headers for the request. The response is then parsed as text and any errors are caught and handled.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/website/docs/bigbot/step-4-bot.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
BOT.gateway.requestMembers = async function (guildId, options) {
    await fetch(process.env.GATEWAY_MANAGER_URL, {
        method: "POST",
        headers: {
            "Content-Type": "application/json",
            "Authorization": process.env.AUTHORIZATION,
        },
        body: JSON.stringify({ type: "REQUEST_MEMBERS", guildId, options });
    })
        .then(res => res.text())
        .catch(() => undefined);
}
```

