TITLE: Configuring Desired Properties Example
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to configure `desiredProperties` within the `createBot` function in Discordeno. It specifies that only `id`, `toggles` (containing the 'bot' flag), and `username` properties should be cached for user objects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/website/docs/desired-properties.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const bot = createBot({
  // Your usual createBot options, such as token and intents
  desiredProperties: {
