TITLE: Filtering Useless MESSAGE_UPDATE Events Typescript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet implements a cache to ignore redundant `MESSAGE_UPDATE` events. It compares the current message content with a cached version and only processes the event if the content has changed, significantly reducing CPU usage in scenarios with frequent embed or link updates.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/website/docs/bigbot/step-3-gateway.md#_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
if (payload.t === 'MESSAGE_UPDATE') {
  const message = payload.d as DiscordMessage

  const id = message.id
  const content = message.content || ''
  const cached = cache.editedMessages.get(id)

  if (cached === content) return
  else {
    // Add to local cache for future events comparison
    cache.editedMessages.set(id, content)
    // Remove after 10 seconds from cache
    setTimeout(() => {
      cache.editedMessages.delete(id)
    }, 10000)
  }
}
```

