TITLE: Handling READY Event for Guild Caching Typescript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet captures the `READY` event and stores the initial guild IDs in the `loadingGuildIds` cache. This cache is used to identify guilds the bot is already in when it starts, preventing duplicate processing of `GUILD_CREATE` events during startup.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/website/docs/bigbot/step-3-gateway.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
events: {
  async message(shrd, payload) {
    Influx?.writePoint(
      new Point('gatewayEvents')
        .timestamp(new Date())
        .stringField('type', payload.t ?? "NA")
        .tag('shard', shardId),
    );

    if (payload.t === "READY") {
      // Marks which guilds the bot in when initial loading in cache
      payload.d.guilds.forEach((g) => cache.loadingGuildIds.add(g.id));
    }

    await fetch(getUrlFromShardId(req.body.totalShards, shard.id), {
+     method: 'POST',
+     headers: {
+       'Content-Type': 'application/json',
+       authorization: AUTHORIZATION,
+     },
+     body: JSON.stringify({ payload, shardId: shard.id }),
+   })
+     .then(res => res.text())
+     .catch(logger.error)
  },
},
```

