SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/website/docs/contributing.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
yarn test:unit
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Run Unit Tests with Coverage
DESCRIPTION: This command runs unit tests and generates a coverage report. It helps identify areas of the code that are not adequately tested.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
yarn test:unit-coverage
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Install Yarn Globally
DESCRIPTION: This command installs Yarn globally using npm. Yarn is used as the package manager and workspace manager for the Discordeno project. This is a prerequisite for setting up the workspace.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
npm install -g yarn
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Install Yarn using Corepack
DESCRIPTION: This command enables Corepack, a tool to manage Yarn versions, ensuring the correct version is used for the project.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/website/docs/contributing.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
corepack enable
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Run Unit Tests on All Packages
DESCRIPTION: This command runs unit tests on all packages within the Discordeno project. This is a crucial step to verify the correctness and reliability of the code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
yarn test:unit
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Installing Dependencies with Yarn
DESCRIPTION: This command installs all the necessary dependencies for the project using Yarn. It reads the dependencies from the package.json file and installs them into the node_modules directory.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/examples/bigbot/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
yarn
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Check Test File Types
DESCRIPTION: This command checks TypeScript types specifically for test files. This ensures that the test code is also type-safe.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
yarn test:test-type
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Starting the Bot with Yarn
DESCRIPTION: This command starts the main bot process using the yarn script defined in package.json.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/examples/bigbot/README.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
yarn start:bot
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Check Code Style
DESCRIPTION: This command checks the code style using a linter. It ensures that the code adheres to the project's coding standards.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
yarn lint
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Build Documentation for Website
DESCRIPTION: This command builds the documentation for the Discordeno website. This ensures that the website always has the latest documentation available.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
yarn build:doc
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Install Project Dependencies
DESCRIPTION: This command installs all project dependencies using Yarn. It is necessary to run this command to set up the workspace after cloning the repository.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
yarn install
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Format Code
DESCRIPTION: This command formats the code automatically. It helps maintain a consistent code style throughout the project.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
yarn fmt
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Starting the Gateway with Yarn
DESCRIPTION: This command starts the Discord gateway process using the yarn script defined in package.json. It handles the real-time communication with Discord's gateway.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/examples/bigbot/README.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
yarn start:gateway
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Starting the REST Proxy with Yarn
DESCRIPTION: This command starts the REST proxy using the yarn script defined in package.json. It's responsible for handling REST API requests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/examples/bigbot/README.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
yarn start:rest
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Install Corepack Globally via NPM
DESCRIPTION: This command installs Corepack globally using npm, which is necessary if Corepack is not already available in your environment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/website/docs/contributing.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
npm install -g corepack
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Build Static Website
DESCRIPTION: This command builds the Docusaurus website into static content, which is then placed in the `build` directory. This output is suitable for deployment to any static content hosting service. No dependencies other than the installed yarn packages are required.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/website/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Shell
CODE:
```
$ yarn build
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Import React Component in Markdown
DESCRIPTION: This snippet imports a custom React component named 'Benchmark' from the '@site/src/components/Benchmark' path. This allows the Markdown file to render the React component.
SOURCE: https://github.com/discordeno/discordeno/blob/main/website/docs/benchmark.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Markdown
CODE:
```
import Benchmark from '@site/src/components/Benchmark'
```
